OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1772012418
OL,3,CDonald Trump says countries are
OL,4,C'happy' with tariffs as he vows to
OL,5,Ckeep them
OL,7,FSpeaking at his State of the Union
OL,8,Faddress before a joint session of
OL,9,FCongress at the US Capitol in
OL,10,FWashington DC, Mr Trump said: "Almost
OL,11,Fall countries and corporations want to
OL,12,Fkeep the deal that they already made.
OL,14,F"Knowing that the legal power that I,
OL,15,Fas president, have to make a new deal
OL,16,Fcould be far worse for them,
OL,17,Ftherefore, they'll continue to work
OL,18,Falongside the same successful path
OL,19,Fthat we had negotiated before the
OL,20,Fcourt's unfortunate involvement.
OL,26,@rD@_OUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
